<font color="#FF0000">RACISM, REALITY, AND ONIONS !</font><br>
<tt>Sat Apr 26 14:46:22 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Well, you need a seatbelt when you drive on this thread on Friday night. At least some adult beverages.  I have never been called a racist before, or for that matter, discribed as an onion.  Both give me pause to think<br><br>
Racism, the topic we all seemed to have flamed on/over, is a very ugly topic, and issue, and can take the form of descracrating cemetaries, burning crosses, or more subtle forms, like denying jobs, houses, loans, or even more subtle, holding someone or some group up to a different standard, a different level of thinking. Be it better or worse, higher or lower, when you think about a group of people in a different manner intellectually, or hold that group to a different level of rules, that too is racism, only very subtle.<br><br>
DocDel: When you wrote last night that: &quot;You, a Jew, would even spew that garbage from day one. I tell you, Barry, that I did not know you were Jewish, and now that I do, I am<br>
so GOD DAMN PISSED at you.&quot;  Why Doc?  Because you are judging me by different standards the minute you found out I was Jewish.  Don't I have the American right to be a redneck racist (if I was one), even if I am Jewish?  You made the equation that being Jewish meant that I must be super-sensitive to racial issues, cause all Jews are.  That is class-think, and subtle racism.  Really DocDel, your anger is that you expect something &quot;more&quot; from me than Chet, Tom, or anyone else, and I failed you, I let you down by being average or normal.  Maybe my parents just Americanized me too well, and now I have American prejudices just like my Christian or Muslim neighbors.<br><br>
This is not unique to you, Doc, hell the world does it. Israel is regularily held up to &quot;higher&quot; standards and rules than the Arab countries that surround it.  Arab's blow up 100's of Jewish kids and women, and the Media plays it as an average day. A Jewish nut cuts loose with an M-16 in a Mosque and the media flips out for weeks.  Other countries get to keep the spoils of war, the United Nations just voted yesterday to tell Israel that it can not build houses in East Jerusalem.  How many other countries have the U.N. dictating home construction?  See what I mean.  At the risk of a bad pun, DocDel, I didn't pull the foreskin over your eyes, you already had it there for whatever reasons, sorry I just acted like an average human being, but that's all I am. <br><br>
As for being an onion.  I don't know.  I think that while I meant it when I said I left my shingle at the door, I am still the product of 25 years of shrinkdom. It has changed me, changed my thinking, changed how I deal with my emotions, and those of others.  I can't help that.  25 years of being in the mental 'health' business has done things to me, for better or worse, level upon level, I guess. So, Chet, I don't know what or who may be at the core.  I guess an onion's role is to spice things up, bring a tear or two to the eyes when cut, and cause heartburn (at least with me it does).  I'll take it as a compliment, if you don't mind. Better than being called a grapefruit or a bananna.<br><br>
Doc Spatz<br><br>

